hep.20436&amp;pmid=15486923">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">73.</div><div id="R73" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Gandini</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">R</span></span>, Konda D, Simonetti G. Transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunt patency and clinical outcome in patients with Budd-Chiari syndrome: covered versus uncovered stents. <em>Radiology</em>2006; 241(1): 298–305.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.2411050347">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16908675/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Radiology&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;pages=298&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiol.2411050347&amp;pmid=16908675">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/29/3" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2009.29.issue-3/asset/14a168ae-c214-168a-9c21-a168ae9c214a/radiographics.2009.29.issue-3.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">669</span> - <span property="pageEnd">681</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19448109/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19448109</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.293085056">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IVC+%3D+inferior+vena+cava&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IVC = inferior vena cava</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=TIPS+%3D+transjugular+intrahepatic+portosystemic+shunt&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">TIPS = transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunt</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The clinical, pathologic, and venographic features of Budd-Chiari syndrome are described and illustrated, and possible outcomes after treatment with medical, surgical, and endovascular methods are discussed.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Marco</span> <span property="familyName">Cura</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas Health Science Center, 7703 Floyd Curl Dr, Mail Code 7800, San Antonio, TX 78229-3900 (M.C., J.L.); and Department of Radiology, Columbia University Medical Center, New York, NY (Z.H.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 17, 2008; revision requested April 23 and received August 20; accepted August 21. Z.H. is a member of the advisory boards of W. L. Gore &amp; Associates, AngioDynamics, Elcam, OmniSonics Medical Technologies, and North-Point Domain and a consultant for C. R. Bard, Boston Scientific, and NovaShunt, and has received royalties from Microtek International and Cook Group. All other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Cura/Marco" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Ziv</span> <span property="familyName">Haskal</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span><sup class="xref">2</sup></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas Health Science Center, 7703 Floyd Curl Dr, Mail Code 7800, San Antonio, TX 78229-3900 (M.C., J.L.); and Department of Radiology, Columbia University Medical Center, New York, NY (Z.H.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 17, 2008; revision requested April 23 and received August 20; accepted August 21. Z.H. is a member of the advisory boards of W. L. Gore &amp; Associates, AngioDynamics, Elcam, OmniSonics Medical Technologies, and North-Point Domain and a consultant for C. R. Bard, Boston Scientific, and NovaShunt, and has received royalties from Microtek International and Cook Group. All other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Haskal/Ziv" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con3" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Jorge</span> <span property="familyName">Lopera</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, University of Texas Health Science Center, 7703 Floyd Curl Dr, Mail Code 7800, San Antonio, TX 78229-3900 (M.C., J.L.); and Department of Radiology, Columbia University Medical Center, New York, NY (Z.H.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 17, 2008; revision requested April 23 and received August 20; accepted August 21. Z.H. is a member of the advisory boards of W. L. Gore &amp; Associates, AngioDynamics, Elcam, OmniSonics Medical Technologies, and North-Point Domain and a consultant for C. R. Bard, Boston Scientific, and NovaShunt, and has received royalties from Microtek International and Cook Group. All other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Lopera/Jorge" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this autho